About
An iconic destination in Lower Manhattan, Brookfield Place brings together an eclectic mix of cultural and art experiences, a stellar line-up of events, delectable dining options and world-class shopping all in one destination.
Duration: More than 3 hours

An upmarket mall with great air conditioning!
Jul 2023 Couples
We stopped by Brookfield Place for a bite to eat after a morning exploring in lower Manhattan. Having been lapping up the early morning sun, walking through the doors into the cool clean atmosphere of the airy and vibrant mall was a welcome break from the humid streets.

With plenty of options for food, both my partner and I opted for different offerings and then soaked up the atmosphere whilst watching the world go by. The mall is wonderful, the large glass windows presenting the most stunning natural light accompanied with the indoor greenery really makes for a great atmosphere.

After we'd eaten a stroll through the shops for a bit of retail therapy was absolutely the right decision for the afternoon.
Written December 21, 2023

Indoor Mall With Good Restaurants Including Le District and Naya
Nov 2022
Upscale shopping mall at 9/11 memorial site. Restaurants, shops, and access to Oculus shops below. Outstanding views of Hudson River plus outside promenade for walks and relaxing (in warm weather). Ferry to New Jersey nearby. Events often scheduled at central indoor plaza. French style food court below. More ubiquitous food court on upper level. I ate at both - lighter snack style and coffee at Le District and a tasty lamb kebab bowl at Naya upstairs.
Written December 12, 2022

Gorgeous High-End Shopping Center
Dec 2021
We generally stay in the financial district when visiting NYC, so Brookfield Place is an obvious choice for a place to go. The mall is spacious, very clean and well maintained, and has a variety of upscale shops and restaurants. It opens out onto the Hudson, with great views of New Jersey and the Statue of Liberty. When the weather is nice, you can sit outside to eat, drink and take in the view.

Location is convenient to the World Trade Center and 9-11 Memorial.
Written January 4, 2022

Buenos Aires, Argentina2,935 contributions
We went to see a temporary exhibit in the halls of the shopping center. Nice!
Nov 2021 Friends
Every year in the pre-Thanksgiving period, Brookfield Place houses Can-struction: in league with a food drive for the needy prior to the big holiday. Artists are asked to create sculptures made out of canned goods. They are scattered through the two floors of the shopping complex. Very clever!

The mall itself is made up of very high-end brands. All very elegant and expensive. There is an interesting foodcourt/foodmarket.

Worth a visit.
Written November 17, 2021
